reviews.review_text:
Great source/underrated show Best-sounding source available (to these ears)...great work again by CM et al...

First Smokestack in ages?...crowd goes bonkers...Jerry riffs hard...Fine JackStraw and a pretty darn good Help-Slip-Frank, '84 style.

underrated year and show...great sound!

Johns Birthday... They seemed to pull out some stops on John Lennon's birthday.  This one seemed to me to be an obvious tribute from the Dancin' start to the Revolution finish.  Cut down a man in cold blood Shannon, might as well be me...into a He's Gone that was just tremendous.  around & around into Johnny B. Goode...because its only rock and roll...right!

The recording quality sounds like a typical east coast arena, boomy and noisy.  But damn some good times were had in those said arenas.

God Bless the Grateful Dead!

If ya think this is good, try 4/27/84 with the 2nd set playin high time etc something or other, and some say 84 was not so great, but there is also 10/12/84 and 10/20/84

in fact it was better than the 85 supposplayin Muzak
Best Aud source The Rolfe 700 is nice too, but this has better warmth and balance.
